headline.main: PHILADELPHIA.; Reprehensible Manner of Burying the Dead--Vegetarian Banquet--Weather, Business. THE LIGHTNING-ROD AT NEWARK. Second Letter from Mr. Quimby. The Military Excursion of the Bininger Guards. Their trip to Niagara Falls-Return, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: The weather continues between wind and rain, with the thermometer at 84[degrees]. Everything is dull, and news very scarce. The Fall trade commenced a few weeks earlier than usual this year, but the business has not been as large as was at first anticipated.

byline.original: Correspondence of the New-York Daily Times.EDWARD E. QUIMBY

headline.main: City Health and Mortality of the Week.

docs.lead_paragraph: The City has been blessed with health through the week. The physicians who are old and rich enough to speak unhesitatingly, affirm that there is very little sickness prevalent. The story is less flattering as we descend to the youngest and most needy members of the profession.
docs.snippet: The City has been blessed with health through the week. The physicians who are old and rich enough to speak unhesitatingly, affirm that there is very little sickness prevalent. The story is less flattering as we descend to the youngest and most needy...

docs.lead_paragraph: The Board of Health, finding some difficulty obtaining full reports of the prevailing disease from the physicians of the city, have determined to report the interments for each day. The public may rely implicitly on the published reports, as the Board will receive full returns from all the undertakers of the city.
